1
00:00:00,733 --> 00:00:01,900
The cop's all over social media.

2
00:00:01,900 --> 00:00:03,467
<i>They just found her body.
She's dead.</i>

3
00:00:03,467 --> 00:00:05,700
I wouldn't be surprised if Andy
was the one who had her killed.

4
00:00:05,700 --> 00:00:07,100
<i> Who killed Marina?</i>

5
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:08,467
<i> Do I have other enemies?</i>

6
00:00:09,267 --> 00:00:11,300
<i> Andy, let's talk!</i>

7
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,400
<i> You killed my son.</i>

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,767
<i> You and that policewoman.</i>

9
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:18,633
<i>I'm not in the video because
I had nothing to do with it.</i>

10
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:20,433
<i>We're on the same side,
aren't we?</i>

11
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:21,567
[GRUNTS]

12
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:22,733
[LEON SCREAMING]

13
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:24,333
<i> Is anyone there?</i>

14
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:27,500
<i> Huh?!</i>

15
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,333
<i>- Leon!
- Monette!</i>

16
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,233
<i>Oh my God!
What happened to you?</i>

17
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> No--</i>

18
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:35,433
<i>- Monette, no!
- Let Leon go!</i>

19
00:00:35,467 --> 00:00:37,133
[MONETTE SCREAMING]

20
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,500
[GRUNTING]

21
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:42,300
[LEON BREATHING HEAVILY]

22
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:43,467
<i> Monette!</i>

23
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,433
[CRYING] Monette!

24
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:57,067
Hello, Philippines!
And hello, world!

25
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:58,033
Good morning, ma'am!

26
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,700
- Good morning.
- If you need anything,

27
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,400
just call my name and
I'll be there.

28
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:04,167
- Raphie at your service.
- Alright, thanks, Raphie.

29
00:01:04,367 --> 00:01:05,800
Thank you, ma'am.

30
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,500
- Nathalie!
- Yes?

31
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:10,200
Please assist Miss... Pretty!

32
00:01:14,167 --> 00:01:15,500
Such a beautiful morning.

33
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,767
It's burnt!

34
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:34,100
I told you, I should've done it.

35
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,133
[KIKO]
This is what I'm talking about!

36
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:38,133
Why only two eggs?
What about me?

37
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:39,767
- Cook it yourself!
- Fine, I'll do it.

38
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:44,433
You said you were good at this.

39
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:46,433
I said I'm good at cooking rice.

40
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,267
I never said I could cook.

41
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:50,533
So you're just a
rice cooker king, huh?

42
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,300
Hey, sir!

43
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,433
What kind of mess is this?
What's going on?

44
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:59,500
Isn't it obvious?
We're cooking.

45
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,700
[RAPHIE SCOFFS]

46
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:02,833
I know, that's obvious.

47
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,633
But why you guys?
Where's Monette?

48
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:07,700
Hmm... she's not here yet.

49
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:10,400
Maybe she overslept.

50
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,767
We couldn't wait anymore.
We're hungry.

51
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:15,433
Overslept?
I thought she was up early.

52
00:02:15,467 --> 00:02:17,567
When I checked her bed
earlier,

53
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:18,733
she wasn't there.

54
00:02:20,367 --> 00:02:22,200
But you slept together
last night?

55
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:24,167
I don't really know.

56
00:02:24,167 --> 00:02:25,500
I went to bed early, sir.

57
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,567
[MARTIN] So where is she?

58
00:02:28,567 --> 00:02:29,833
I'll call her.

59
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:33,500
She's probably around,
chatting with a guest.

60
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,533
- [LINE RINGING]
- This might get cold.

61
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:36,700
Kiko.

62
00:02:37,667 --> 00:02:40,467
- Raphie, did she pick up?
- [LINE RINGING]

63
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:42,667
No, sir. It just keeps ringing.

64
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:45,267
- Where is she?
- Maybe she's...

65
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:46,367
[LINE RINGING]

66
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:48,333
[MARTIN]
I'll ask the other staff.

67
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:53,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:02:55,800 --> 00:03:02,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,733
[SIGHS]

70
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:58,400
Luna...

71
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,467
Have you called
your brother again?

72
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,500
Mom, I just called him
five minutes ago.

73
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:04,300
Call him again.

74
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:10,000
[LINE BEEPING]

75
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,733
Eat first, Mom.

76
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,200
Still nothing, Mom.

77
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:19,833
Maybe he lost signal
or his phone died.

78
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,667
He'll find out what's
going on here, Mom.

79
00:04:22,667 --> 00:04:24,267
He'll come home.

80
00:04:24,733 --> 00:04:27,533
Oh God, what's happening
to your brother?

81
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,700
[LUNA] Mom...

82
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:30,733
nothing bad is going
to happen to him.

83
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,033
But I have a bad feeling.

84
00:04:33,033 --> 00:04:34,567
I can't explain it.

85
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:38,400
With all these killings
happening on the island...

86
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,533
Mom, stop it!

87
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:42,767
- Don't think like that.
- How can I not?

88
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:45,400
I'm a mother!

89
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:50,467
I can feel it when my child
is in danger!

90
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:51,933
Please!

91
00:04:52,567 --> 00:04:54,333
Just trust Leon, okay?

92
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:56,567
You know...

93
00:04:56,567 --> 00:04:58,833
this just proves why he didn't
call us first when he escaped.

94
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:00,700
- Because of you!
- Justin, enough.

95
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:11,567
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:18,800
[SOBBING]

97
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,933
[HEAVY BREATHING]

98
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:28,700
I just took the rest
of my stuff.

99
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:30,933
I see.

100
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:33,733
So you're really
not coming back?

101
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,833
Aren't you going to ask
where I'm going?

102
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:43,367
Alright.

103
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:45,833
Fine.

104
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:47,467
Where?

105
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:50,033
To Hotel 88.

106
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:52,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:54,300
Why would you go back there?

108
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,433
What for?

109
00:06:05,067 --> 00:06:07,700
I want to make things right.

110
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:16,500
I'm going with you.

111
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:20,700
You don't have to.

112
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,800
I want to hear what you're
going to tell them.

113
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

114
00:06:26,967 --> 00:06:28,567
Ask around too.

115
00:06:28,567 --> 00:06:29,867
See if anyone's seen Monette.

116
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:32,133
Yes, sir.

117
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:36,700
[PHONE VIBRATING]

118
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,533
Luna.

119
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,733
Hey, Martin.

120
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:43,800
Did Leon call or text you?

121
00:06:44,633 --> 00:06:45,800
[MARTIN] Not yet.

122
00:06:46,467 --> 00:06:51,100
Ask him. Maybe Leon
went back to the place

123
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:53,567
he and Leon talked about--

124
00:06:53,567 --> 00:06:55,900
Martin, did you hear that?

125
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:57,033
Yeah.

126
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:58,033
Sorry, Luna.

127
00:06:58,033 --> 00:07:00,533
I already called my contact
at the condo.

128
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,567
He never arrived there.

129
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,733
Martin, we're really worried.

130
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,667
[MARTIN] I am too.

131
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,000
Everything's piling up.

132
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,000
Even Monette left
without saying anything.

133
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:14,500
Monette's missing?

134
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:16,667
- Oh my God.
- Mom.

135
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:18,600
[MARTIN]<i> N-no.
</i> Don't panic too much.

136
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:20,933
<i>She's only been gone
a short while.</i>

137
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,867
But that's not like Monette.

138
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,067
She wouldn't leave
without telling anyone.

139
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:31,167
Monette knows this island well.

140
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:33,433
She wouldn't just get lost.

141
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,833
[MARTIN] Justin's right.

142
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:39,033
Alright, Martin,
keep us updated, okay?

143
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,433
Okay. Bye.

144
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:44,767
[BEEPS]

145
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,767
Even Monette is missing?

146
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:53,633
Let's stay positive, okay?

147
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:54,867
But Justin...

148
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,067
Positive, Jade.

149
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,467
Those who aren't coming come,
will go home!

150
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,700
Just like Leon.
He will come home.

151
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:12,767
[TRIXIE] Raphie,
they won't stop looking.

152
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:14,767
All of the other staff
have been informed.

153
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:16,867
Okay? We'll find her.
We'll find her.

154
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:20,533
- What if-
- Raphie.

155
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,667
Raphie.

156
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:24,600
Don't think like that.

157
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,033
Stop that.

158
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:28,500
Shh.

159
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:31,667
Do you want
to report it to the police?

160
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:35,567
Cheska, it hasn't been 24 hours
since Monette went missing.

161
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:37,600
They might not entertain us.

162
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:41,200
No, okay. Well, let's...
let's just think positive.

163
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,767
Monette is just there.

164
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:45,533
She's alive and well.

165
00:08:45,533 --> 00:08:47,500
I feel different.

166
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:53,700
I feel like you'll
all disagree, but...

167
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,933
do you want to go
to my grandpa's?

168
00:08:58,533 --> 00:09:00,500
He might know where she is.

169
00:09:01,233 --> 00:09:04,700
Sari, Martin has already
warned us about that.

170
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:06,700
If he finds out about this...

171
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,600
Let's not mention it to him.

172
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,233
He doesn't need to know.

173
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,567
Come on,
let's do this for Raphie.

174
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:17,600
So?

175
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:19,633
Should we go?

176
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:25,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

177
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:27,167
[DOOR OPENS]

178
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:31,167
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

179
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:38,167
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

180
00:09:53,167 --> 00:10:00,100
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

181
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:15,333
- How's it going?
- There's no news on Monette.

182
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:17,367
When was the last time
you saw her?

183
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:18,967
Last night.

184
00:10:18,967 --> 00:10:20,667
Did she sleep here?

185
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:22,967
We don't know.
Raphie went to bed early.

186
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,133
When he woke up,

187
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,767
Monette was either not there
or hadn't arrived in bed yet

188
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,933
- What about Leon?
- He's not yet here.

189
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:32,700
Mom is worried.

190
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,733
We didn't know how to
calm her down.

191
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:36,300
How about you don't scold her?

192
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:38,733
- I-I was just trying to...
- No, Justin!

193
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:40,167
Why don't you be
a bit more understanding?

194
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:43,000
Fine!

195
00:10:48,067 --> 00:10:49,333
Is that Andy?

196
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:56,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

197
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:07,633
Go, Dad.

198
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:09,767
Tell them.

199
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:11,500
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,667
Admit it.

201
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:14,767
[ANDY INHALES DEEPLY]

202
00:11:14,767 --> 00:11:15,800
Okay.

203
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:20,400
I wanted to be part
of Hotel 88...

204
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,400
because of the treasure.

205
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,467
We won't pretend
to be surprised.

206
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,700
[MARTIN]
Because we already know that.

207
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:31,733
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:35,200
This was part of our plan,
with Michael and Fred.

209
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:40,400
I just wanted to finish what
my friends and I started.

210
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:42,867
Friends?

211
00:11:43,733 --> 00:11:44,833
Since when?

212
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:45,967
[ANDY] Ever since.

213
00:11:45,967 --> 00:11:48,533
But you weren't really around
back then, remember?

214
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:49,533
The three of you.

215
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:51,700
[ANDY] So you couldn't
have known about it.

216
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:55,300
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

217
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,433
Look, I can honestly say
that I was devastated

218
00:11:57,433 --> 00:11:59,267
when I found out
they had died.

219
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:04,000
And I can say that while
looking all of you in the eye.

220
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:12,033
So, when will you confess
to framing Leon?

221
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:17,300
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:19,000
I didn't set him up.

223
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:21,467
I didn't kill Juan.

224
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,867
It was all that cop's handiwork,
that Marina.

225
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:25,500
She killed Juan.

226
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:26,567
By following your orders.

227
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:28,267
I don't know Marina personally.

228
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:31,500
I can't claim to know
her motive for killing Juan.

229
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,667
I've barely even spoken
to her!

230
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:40,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:45,533
Okay.

232
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:50,767
I admit to using Leon's
weakness with family

233
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,900
against him.

234
00:12:52,433 --> 00:12:53,633
And, yes, that was wrong of me.

235
00:12:53,633 --> 00:12:54,900
I made a mistake.

236
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,100
But I was only human,

237
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:00,833
blinded by the promise
of treasure.

238
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,867
Look, I may be a lot
of things, but...

239
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,533
I am not a murderer.

240
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:10,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,300
[GIO] That's it?

242
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,367
Got anything else to say?

243
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:15,033
Anything else that
you want to confess?

244
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:19,567
Just... please believe me.

245
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:22,033
In that case,
you may leave now.

246
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:32,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,000
[SIGHS] Now, buddy...

248
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,033
I did the right thing.

249
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,367
I came clean.

250
00:13:55,400 --> 00:14:02,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:07,533
[LIQUID DRIPPING]

252
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,833
What else do you want from me?

253
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,933
Why didn't you just kill me?

254
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,933
Don't be impatient.

255
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:22,733
We'll get there soon enough.

256
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:27,033
For now, there's still much
I expect you to tell me.

257
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,433
Like what?

258
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:32,067
Let's put an end to this.

259
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:35,700
Like how your brother
fits into all of this.

260
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:39,633
Leave my family out of this.

261
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,200
They have nothing
to do with anything.

262
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,933
Any one of them.

263
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:46,500
[LOUD THUD]

264
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,500
That Justin!

265
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,000
What did he do to my son?

266
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:53,033
He didn't do anything.

267
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:55,767
All he did was
offer Juan friendship.

268
00:14:55,767 --> 00:14:57,033
A friend?!

269
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:00,767
He helped your son look
for you.

270
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:03,967
There are some missing items
in my house.

271
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:05,467
Did he take them?!

272
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:07,100
[LEON]
Justin didn't take anything.

273
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,033
But I did.

274
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:11,167
Your burner phone.

275
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:13,067
Your picture with Uncle Andy.

276
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:15,600
What else?

277
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,100
[LEON] I already told you.

278
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:20,100
Those are the only things
I took.

279
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:24,000
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

280
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,700
- [SCREAMS]
- [SLAMS TABLE]

281
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:36,433
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

282
00:15:37,767 --> 00:15:40,667
He didn't admit
what he did to Leon.

283
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:43,500
He also denied that
he knows De La Paz personally.

284
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,733
[JUSTIN]
He gave us nothing useful.

285
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,867
[MARTIN] He did.

286
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:48,733
Even though we've known it
for a long time,

287
00:15:48,733 --> 00:15:51,033
at least we finally heard
from his own mouth

288
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,100
that he believes
the treasure exists.

289
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:57,833
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

290
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:59,833
He confessed to some things
and tried to act innocent.

291
00:16:00,533 --> 00:16:03,567
He also claimed that he was
very close to our fathers.

292
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,800
Could it be that he thinks he
might get part of the treasure,

293
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,633
since his relationship
with them was good?

294
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:13,067
[GIO] Kiko might be right.

295
00:16:13,767 --> 00:16:16,633
Therefore, we shouldn't be
wasting our time.

296
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:19,233
We need to find
the treasure now.

297
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,167
No more bluffing.

298
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:24,100
We need to get it done, ASAP.

299
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,700
For everyone's safety.

300
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,233
And again,

301
00:16:29,067 --> 00:16:31,833
for justice for the deaths
of our fathers.

302
00:16:31,833 --> 00:16:37,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

303
00:16:37,967 --> 00:16:41,900
[MUSIC SWELLING]

304
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:44,333
[DOOR OPENS]

305
00:16:44,633 --> 00:16:47,100
You said you were going
to make things right!

306
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:48,533
- I did!
- You lied!

307
00:16:49,533 --> 00:16:51,400
It's true
that Fred was my friend.

308
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,467
What about the cop?

309
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,600
You said you didn't know her!

310
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:56,967
She called you many times!

311
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:58,267
She was updating you about Leon!

312
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,967
I heard it myself!

313
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:02,000
What do you want?
To say all that to them?

314
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,533
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:17:03,533 --> 00:17:05,533
That is what you promised me.

316
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,433
That you were
going to confess...

317
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:13,133
all the bad things you've done.

318
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:18,500
What kind of confession
do you really want from me?

319
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,700
Tell me, Edward.

320
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:22,433
A confession that will ruin me?
Is that it?

321
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:25,133
Do you want me to turn myself in

322
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:27,300
just for the fact
that I paid Marina

323
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:30,533
to update me on what's
going on with Leon in jail?!

324
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:40,400
I don't know you anymore, Dad.

325
00:17:43,533 --> 00:17:44,667
I don't know you anymore.

326
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,733
You can say what you want.

327
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,700
At the end of the day,
I'm still your father.

328
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,967
Exactly!

329
00:17:57,467 --> 00:17:58,633
That sucks.

330
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:03,133
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:05,733
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

332
00:18:05,733 --> 00:18:08,300
Bring those who are hidden
into the light.

333
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,467
To be able to talk...

334
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:13,100
to those we can't see.

335
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:18,000
Guide the path
of those who seek.

336
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,000
[POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:23,033
Bring those who are hidden
into the light.

338
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:26,433
To be able to talk
to those we can't see.

339
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:31,033
Guide the path...

340
00:18:33,767 --> 00:18:35,300
of those who seek.

341
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:38,233
[CLANKING]

342
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:46,267
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

343
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:49,033
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

344
00:18:54,600 --> 00:19:01,533
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

345
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:09,200
[SCREAMS] Aah! [BODY THUDS]

346
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,600
Uh, did you see anything?

347
00:19:24,167 --> 00:19:25,433
I didn't-- I...

348
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:28,367
I didn't see anything.

349
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:30,600
I can't...

350
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:35,433
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:37,267
I couldn't speak to your sister.

352
00:19:37,267 --> 00:19:38,600
I couldn't reach her.

353
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,167
Is that so?

354
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:49,267
Alright. Uh...

355
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,133
we'll head home.

356
00:19:51,133 --> 00:19:52,100
Come on.

357
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,200
Sorry, guys.

358
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:59,100
[TRIXIE] It's okay, Sari.
At least we tried.

359
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:00,533
I'm sorry.

360
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,567
It was weak on my end.

361
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,733
Alright. We'll get going.

362
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:14,800
Dear.

363
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:20,467
Listen to what your gut
tells you.

364
00:20:23,333 --> 00:20:24,667
You know the truth.

365
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:32,233
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:38,400
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

367
00:20:39,267 --> 00:20:40,367
A-Alright.

368
00:20:40,933 --> 00:20:41,900
Thank you.

369
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:52,767
[SNIFFLES]

370
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:55,833
[VOICE BREAKING] Monette...

371
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:57,400
Monette...

372
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:00,767
[SOBBING] My sister...

373
00:21:00,767 --> 00:21:02,767
[SNIFFLES] Monette...

374
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,367
[SNIFFLING, CRYING]

375
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,867
Monette...

376
00:21:10,867 --> 00:21:15,900
[MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL]

377
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,267
Help!

378
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:20,233
[WOMAN PANTING, WHIMPERING]

379
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,533
Help, please!

380
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,767
Help!

381
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:34,600
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

382
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:47,867
Grandpa.

383
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,233
You can say it.

384
00:21:51,767 --> 00:21:53,700
What do you want me to say?

385
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:58,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

386
00:21:58,100 --> 00:22:00,467
Grandpa, I know you.

387
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:02,267
I know you saw
something earlier.

388
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:04,233
I didn't see anything.

389
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,933
[SARI SIGHS]

390
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:08,433
Grandpa, please.

391
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,433
What did the candle say?

392
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:13,267
Where's Monette?

393
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:17,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

394
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:19,033
My dear...

395
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:25,400
Your friend's sister is gone.

396
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:27,400
She's dead.

397
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:35,067
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

398
00:22:35,067 --> 00:22:36,100
Sari.

399
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:38,133
Sari!

400
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:40,467
Sari!

401
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:41,767
Do everything in your power

402
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:44,000
to hold those
responsible accountable.

403
00:22:45,867 --> 00:22:47,167
[MUSIC FADES]

404
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:51,133
We need to be strong.

405
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,167
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

406
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:54,800
For Raphie.

407
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:56,967
[ZIPPER RASPING]

408
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:09,933
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

409
00:23:09,933 --> 00:23:13,133
[STRETCHER WHEELS RATTLING]

410
00:23:20,167 --> 00:23:21,833
[COP] Let's back off for now.

411
00:23:22,767 --> 00:23:24,200
[CHESKA] Mister--
W-Where is...

412
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,800
- [STAFF MEMBER] I was shocked.
- [CHESKA] Bro.

413
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,900
What's happening?
Why's there a bunch of people?

414
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:29,967
- Bro, what was that about?
- Sir, what's going on?

415
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:30,967
Bro?

416
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:33,300
Who was that?

417
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:36,133
- Sir?
- Where did that come from?

418
00:23:37,933 --> 00:23:39,067
Sir?

419
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:42,100
- Raphie...
- Sir Kiko...

420
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:45,100
What's going on?

421
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,700
[GIO] Raphie...

422
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,233
They found Monette earlier.

423
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,900
[RAPHIE BREATHES DEEPLY]

424
00:23:55,933 --> 00:23:57,033
[GIO] She was in the mangroves.

425
00:23:58,867 --> 00:24:00,167
[SOBBING] Raphie.

426
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:03,100
- Sir...
- [GIO] Raphie...

427
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,033
Monette is dead.

428
00:24:12,733 --> 00:24:14,700
No. No.

429
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,633
That can't be Monette. No.

430
00:24:18,667 --> 00:24:21,200
No. My sister and I will see
each other again!

431
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,767
We'll see each other again!
That can't be her!

432
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:25,967
[CRYING]

433
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:28,000
That's not Monette!

434
00:24:29,233 --> 00:24:32,033
[RAPHIE] Monette! Sir...

435
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:34,867
take that back!
That's not Monette!

436
00:24:35,133 --> 00:24:37,133
That's not Monette!

437
00:24:38,433 --> 00:24:39,967
[CRYING] Monette!

438
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:42,100
No!

439
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:45,033
That's not Monette!

440
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,867
[RAPHIE CRYING] Sir!

441
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:55,667
Monette!

442
00:24:56,733 --> 00:24:59,933
Monette!

443
00:25:03,067 --> 00:25:07,433
Sir, that can't be her!
No! No! No!

444
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:09,867
We will see each other again!

445
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:13,000
Please, sir!

446
00:25:14,033 --> 00:25:16,267
It can't be!

447
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:20,467
<i> Just like Monette.</i>

448
00:25:20,467 --> 00:25:24,000
<i>Alone in the sea but the light
she brings transcends.</i>

449
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:25,833
<i> I hope Raphie
can get through this.</i>

450
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:28,333
<i>We'll seek justice
for Monette's death.</i>

451
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,933
<i>Kiko and your siblings
were right.</i>

452
00:25:30,933 --> 00:25:32,167
<i> This will hurt us both.</i>

453
00:25:32,933 --> 00:25:34,333
Are you going to use that on me?

454
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:36,167
<i> Just kill me.</i>

455
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,767
<i>I promised Leon.
I will protect our family.</i>

456
00:25:38,767 --> 00:25:40,967
I have to fulfill that promise.

457
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:41,933
<i> Oh, forgive me.</i>

458
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,500
<i>But how many more people
are going to die</i>

459
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,133
<i> before we get through this?</i>

460
00:25:45,133 --> 00:25:46,333
<i> You took away my son,</i>

461
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:48,700
<i> so I will take your son too.</i>
